, "text": ", as a name of God, signifies"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "The Mighty,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(TA,)"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "who overcomes"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(O, TA)"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "everything:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(TA:) or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "He who resists,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "withstands, so that nothing overcomes Him:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(Zj, TA:) or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "The Incomparable,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "Unparalleled."}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(TA.) ―         -b4-  It also signifies"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "The King;"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "because he has the mastery over the people of his dominions: (O, K:) and especially"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "the ruler of Misr together with Alexandria;"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(K, TA:) a surname; like"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "Aln~ajaA$iY~u", "text_ar": "النَّجَاشِىُّ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "applied to the King of the Abyssinians, and"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "qayoSarN", "text_ar": "قَيْصَرٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "to the King of the Romans. (TA.) ―         -b5-"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "waA_in~ahu lakitaAbN EaziyzN", "text_ar": "وَاـِنَّهُ لَكِتَابٌ عَزِيزٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", [said of the Kur, in that book, xli. 41, means"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "And verily it is a mighty book:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "meaning,"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "inimitable:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or]"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "defended,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "protected,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(Bd, Jel,)"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "from being rendered void and from being corrupted:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(Bd:) or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "of great utility; unequalled."}, {"kind":